    "caption": "HbA1c is your 3-month blood sugar average.\n\nGlucose sticks to your red blood cells and stays there. The higher your blood sugar, the more sticks.\n\nWhat can help lower it? Consider:\n • Eating in an 8-hour window\n • Starting with fiber and protein\n • Taking short walks after meals\n\nConsistency matters. \n\nTest HbA1c with Function and see patterns, not snapshots.",
