    "caption": "Every November, the NYC Marathon reminds us what the human body is truly capable of – 26.2 miles of endurance, discipline, and power working in sync. But here’s the thing: you don’t need to run 26.2 miles to test your endurance.\n\nEvery day, your body is running its own version of a marathon, from deadlines, workouts, kids, commutes, and stress.\n\nThe difference between those who keep going and those who burn out? It’s how efficiently the body produces energy, manages inflammation, and recovers.\n\nWhen these systems work in sync, your body performs like a well-trained athlete: steady, focused, and resilient.\n\nBut when fatigue hits you midday or it’s getting hard to concentrate at work, that’s your system signaling imbalances and that your cells are working overtime to keep up.",
