    "caption": "HRV has become one of the most tracked health metrics because of wearables, used to guide recovery, training, and sleep. But if you’re eating right, sleeping well, and training consistently yet your HRV doesn’t budge despite these strong habits, it often points to something deeper.\n\nIt’s not about your habits anymore. It’s what’s happening inside your body.\n\nYour HRV reflects how well your body can respond to stress, recover, and maintain balance. When it plateaus, it’s often a sign your recovery systems are under strain: nutrient deficiencies, elevated cortisol, or reduced cellular efficiency can all contribute.\n\nThat’s why HRV should never be looked at in isolation. Your wearable can only show you a number, but deeper bloodwork testing can help explain the “why”.",
