    "shortCode": "DQXEsgtkZEx",
    "caption": "You might notice it every time the seasons change, the low energy, the lack of motivation, the loss of joy in things that usually made you feel good.\n\nIt’s easy to blame it on the shorter days or colder weather.\nBut for some, it’s deeper than that. For some, it’s genetic.\n\nThe MTHFR gene.\nA silent variant carried by nearly 40% of people, most without even knowing it.\n\nWhen this gene isn’t functioning properly, your body struggles to metabolize folate which is a nutrient essential for producing serotonin and dopamine, the very neurotransmitters that regulate mood and motivation.\n\nThat means even if you’re doing everything right like eating well, sleeping enough, exercising, you might still feel off.\n\nDiscover if you have the MTHFR variant and learn how to support your body from the inside out.",
