    "caption": "Noticing more hair going down the drain and a ponytail that feels much skinnier than last year?\n\nHair is one of the body’s most metabolically active tissues, meaning it depends on a steady supply of nutrients and energy. When that supply dips, often from stress, hormonal shifts, or nutrient gaps, your follicles are typically the first to feel it.\n\nBefore reaching for another supplement or hair serum, start with what’s on your plate. Protein, iron, zinc, omega-3s and vitamin D are the raw materials your body uses to grow healthy strands and food delivers them best.\n\nBut if you do need to supplement, do it smarter based on your own body’s data not trends.",
