    "caption": "You don’t feel muscle loss, but it’s happening quietly. Muscle loss doesn’t just begin at old age, it actually starts after your 30s and you’re losing up to 8% of it every decade.\n\nAnd this shift isn’t just affecting your strength or physique, it changes how your body ages, regulates energy, and recovers. In fact, it’s one of the strongest predictors of early death as declining muscle mass single-handedly raises your risk of diabetes, heart disease, osteoporosis, cognitive decline, and frailty.\n\nWhile muscle loss is inevitable, how much you lose isn’t. That’s up to you. A DEXA scan helps you stay ahead of it.",
