    "caption": "Twice a year, we reset our clocks. And with every clock change, we’re disrupting the circadian rhythm our bodies have worked hard to maintain. So if this time change has left you feeling a little off, you’re not imagining it.\n\nWhen we “spring forward”, research shows higher rates of heart attacks, strokes, and fatigue. Fortunately, this fall season, we’ve set our clocks backs which is far less disruptive to our health as we’re giving our bodies more exposure to morning light and a chance to realign with our natural rhythm.\n\nMore light in the morning means steadier energy, better sleep, and fewer risks for cardiovascular strain. This makes us consider how truly important sunlight is for our health.",
